nts on the last poll.The poll puts the Conservatives on 16%, up two points, while the Liberal Democrats are on 9%, up one point, with 6% saying they would vote for others, up one point.The Holyrood list vote was much closer, with the SNP on 29% (down two points), Labour on 28% (down one point) and the Conservatives on 16%, also down one point.The Greens were on 11%, up two points, the Lib Dems on 11%, also up two points, and support for ‚Äúother‚Äù was at 5%, up one point.Analysis by Professor Curtice suggested that if these results were reflected at election time, the SNP would remain the largest party in Holyrood with 46 MSPs.The Labour Party would be a close second with 37 MSPs, and the Conservatives would be reduced to 21 MSPs."
